## Known Issues / Lessons Learned
- IPTV Manager and PVR Simple Client CANNOT be declared as Kodi dependencies — install fails. Users must install them manually.
- PVR Simple Client catchup must be enabled in its settings to use catchup from the TV guide.
- Kodi rejects ZIP install if same version is already installed — Makefile auto-bumps the suffix.
- Sweet.tv API: bulk GetMovieInfo never returns description/duration/channel_id/epg_id; need single-movie call.
- Sweet.tv API: MovieService/GetLink is dead for AVOD content; movies stream via TvService/OpenStream as channel catchups.
- The Linux User-Agent triggered an alternate CDN that returned a media playlist instead of a master playlist; reverted to Windows UA.
- The new x-device header (1;22;39;2;7.4.50) is needed for movies; the old (1;22;0;2;3.7.1) returned empty movie lists.
- Sweet.tv inserts an ad preroll from the unreachable host ads-badtest.sweet.tv. inputstream.adaptive can't recover from it; Kodi's built-in HLS player tolerates it.
- The HLS playlist URL from OpenStream is single-use and expires quickly; can't be cached.
- After clearing addon state on Linux Mint Flatpak, NEVER delete Addons*.db — that wipes all installed addons, not just ours.

## Technical Decisions
- IPTV Manager for native TV section (user choice over rolling our own PVR backend)
- Kodi 21+ only, no legacy support
- Localization: M.NAME constants in strings.py (not bare numeric IDs in code)
- Device pairing auth (not username/password — API requirement)
- Built-in HLS player for streams (NOT inputstream.adaptive — chokes on the ad preroll)
- GNU sed (gsed) used in Makefile, not BSD sed

## Architecture

```
sweet.tv API
    ↕
sweettv_api.py (auth, channels, EPG, streams, movies, search)
    ↕
addon.py (URL router) + service.py (stream cleanup, IPTV Manager bridge)
    ↕
IPTV Manager (channels + EPG via socket)
    ↕
PVR IPTV Simple Client
    ↕
Kodi TV Section
```

## File Layout
```
plugin.video.sweettv/
  addon.xml          - manifest, dependencies
  addon.py           - URL router and all action handlers
  service.py         - background service for stream lifecycle
  icon.png           - addon icon
  resources/
    settings.xml     - addon settings (Kodi 21 v1 schema)
    language/        - en_gb, sk_sk, cs_cz strings.po
    lib/
      sweettv_api.py    - API client
      iptv_manager.py   - IPTV Manager socket integration
      favourites.py     - pinned channels (legacy module name)
      strings.py        - M.NAME localization constants

repository.sweettv/
  addon.xml          - Kodi repo pointer to raw GitHub

repo/
  addons.xml         - generated by `make repo-index`
  addons.xml.md5

docs/
  architecture.md
  api-reference.md
  localization.md
  debugging.md

Makefile             - build, release, version targets
```

## Reference
- Enigma2 plugin: tmp/archivczsk-doplnky/plugin_video_sweettv/ (gitignored)
- sweet.tv API: https://api.sweet.tv/ (all POST, JSON)
- IPTV Manager: https://github.com/add-ons/service.iptv.manager
- PVR Simple Client: https://github.com/kodi-pvr/pvr.iptvsimple
